<PageLayout
  title="Editorial standards"
  kicker="About"
  description="Accuracy and honesty are the whole point of the project."
>
  <p>
    melanocortin.com is an open, educational reference on the melanocortin
    system — the POMC-derived peptides, the MC1R–MC5R receptors, and the
    therapeutics that target them. It is written to serve three audiences on the same pages:
    students and researchers who need mechanism and citations; clinicians and
    curious readers who want an accurate plain-language picture; and anyone
    arriving from a search engine who deserves a credible answer rather than a
    content farm.
  </p>

  <h2>Not medical advice</h2>
  <p>
    Content is for education and general information only. It is not medical
    advice, diagnosis, or treatment, and it is no substitute for a qualified
    clinician. Never disregard professional medical advice, or delay seeking it,
    because of something you read here.
  </p>

  <h2>How we keep pages honest</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Every page carries a visible author and a last-reviewed date.</li>
    <li>
      Therapeutic and clinical-pipeline information dates quickly, and is
      verified against current primary sources before publication.
    </li>
    <li>
      Where the science is uncertain or contested, the page says so — rather
      than papering over it.
    </li>
    <li>
      Claims of fact link to a shared, citeable source registry so readers can
      check the original.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Licensing</h2>
  <p>
    Site content — text and diagrams — is published under
    <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/">Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 (CC BY 4.0)</a>.
    The source code is released under the MIT license. Reuse it; just credit the
    source.
  </p>

  <h2>Corrections</h2>
  <p>
    Found an error or an out-of-date claim? Corrections are welcome and credited.
    The project is in early development — the content model and design system are
    being scaffolded, and pages will be filled in and reviewed over time.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
